{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ed144027-fef1-4f65-88e8-6c52e15750c4","content":"The issue is classic F#: **file compilation order matters**. `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs` in the `.fsproj`, but it depends on types from `Domain.fs`. F# requires dependencies to appear first.\n\nFixing the order:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_014wKqbykGXQLNwmo52Zgt7K","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-afce7907149446e680b4e88864857ddc/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />","new_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-afce7907149446e680b4e88864857ddc/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"35a8728c-0a11-4511-9d74-4d02d6f439e2","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear: In F#, file compilation order matters. Files can only reference modules/types defined in files listed **before** them in the `.fsproj`. \n\nCurrently the order is:\n1. `Services.fs` — depends on `Domain.fs` (uses `Order` type)\n2. `Domain.fs` — defines the types\n3. `Program.fs` — depends on both\n\n`Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`, which is defined in `Domain.fs`. So `Domain.fs` must come first.\n\nThe correct order should be:\n\n\n1. `Domain.fs`\n2. `Services.fs`\n3. `Program.fs`","outputTokens":413,"requestId":"7829:11A527:100E55:1406EA:69F54A5C"},"id":"c7443c0e-3c0f-41f4-9b7e-4e06b531d24f","timestamp":"2026-05-02T00:50:45.950Z","parentId":"f6045f19-b429-47ff-93d0-3e7990fc6b91"}
